Hello! Our team (8825, github) is having some struggles getting pose estimation with Photonvision to work correctly. Our robot is always off by an inconsistent amount than its real position. We are trying to determine the distance between our robot and the center apriltag of the speaker, and use that to determine the angle of our shot. Currently, we have two methods for this.

First, using pose estimation and PhotonUtils.getDistanceToPose(robotPose, targetPose). You can see this here. This distance seems to always be off, but it’s more accurate at further distances. Right up against the speaker, it thinks the robot is in the speaker.

Second, using Photonvision’s PhotonUtils.calculateDistanceToTargetMeters(). You can see this here. (The function getSpecificTargetRange(target) uses calculateDistanceToTargetMeters().) We noticed that as the yaw of the target changes (as our robot spins), photonvision thought the pitch did as well, and then adjusted our estimated distance. We did calibrate the camera and use 3d mode. This is the biggest thing we can’t easily compensate for. We could do the angle math after turning to face the target, but it’s faster if it’s accurate the first time.

That’s how it’s doing right now. I think we can handle the launch angle math, but only if we have an accurate distance measurement. Any idea why we are off? Any help is much appreciated.
